Barely two weeks after Police in Kogi State command paraded 29 suspects arrested over kidnapping and armed robbery on the highways, five other suspects were paraded in Lokoja, yesterday, for kidnapping. In a press statement signed by the Kogi State command police public relation officer (PPRO ), DSP William Aya said: “Five suspected kidnappers who have been terrorising the state have been arrested,” adding that the feat was achieved by the hardworking operatives attached to the Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS). According to Aya , the suspects were arrested based on a tipoff that some criminal elements were sighted in a place negotiating on how to purchase arms and ammunition, in preparation for a kidnapping operation. He added that on the receipt of the tipoff , the operatives swung into action and arrested the following suspects: Idris Haruna, Adamu Abdullahi Yaro, Abdullahi Mohammed Yuguda, Ali Garba and Mohammed Idris. “Kidnappers and other criminals are not spirits,  they are our neighbours, we eat in the same restaurant,  we go to the same market,  same bank. If we continue to shield them from the police, we might become the victim one day,” Aya warned.